Session of 2025
SENATE BILL No. 101
By Senator J.R. Claeys
1-29
1 AN ACT concerning the attorney general; relating to the drug abuse
2 resistance education (D.A.R.E.) program; creating the position of drug
3 abuse resistance education (D.A.R.E.) educator; providing for the
4 duties and responsibilities thereof.
5
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
7 Section 1. (a) The attorney general shall appoint a statewide drug
8 abuse resistance education (D.A.R.E.) educator and, within the limits of
9 appropriations available therefor, such additional staff as necessary to
10 support the functions and responsibilities of the D.A.R.E. educator.
11 (b) The D.A.R.E. educator shall:
12 (1) Provide instruction on drug abuse using a curriculum approved by
13 the attorney general that includes content on fentanyl and other opioid
14 drugs to students in public elementary and secondary schools;
15 (2) report annually to the legislature on any modifications to the
16 curriculum utilized by the attorney general and provide the names and
17 addresses of the public schools serviced by the program; and
18 (3) perform other services and provide material and information as
19 required to support the D.A.R.E. program in Kansas.
20 Sec. 2. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
21 publication in the statute book.

